Math Plotting Homework

2023-08-21

Data

I manually entered data from my math book into vectors to make histograms.

a <- c(550,520,610,600,540,750,250,670,510,590)
s <- c(320, 410, 360, 410, 380, 370, 290, 310, 320, 230)
r <- c(78,78,78,80,85,88,90,92,100)
t <- c(85,85,90,90,92,93,95,97,97,100)
q <- c(10,43,6,15,20,48,68,99,47,28)
w <- c(12,46,8,17,19,45,68,100,48,30)

Plots

I made plots using the function hist and abline to make my histograms.

hist(a, breaks= 10)
abline(v= mean(a), col="purple",lwd=3)

hist(s, breaks= 10)
abline(v= mean(s), col="purple",lwd=3)

hist(r, breaks= 10)
abline(v= mean(r), col="purple",lwd=3)

hist(t, breaks= 10)
abline(v= mean(t), col="purple",lwd=3)

hist(q, breaks= 10)
abline(v= mean(q), col="purple",lwd=3)

hist(w, breaks= 10)
abline(v= mean(w), col="purple",lwd=3)

Note that the echo = FALSE parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.
